Just start and keep going!

6/ Most important thing that helped me keep the streak:

- Having a plan for what I will do on the days that are hard/you're tired/sore/short on time/travelling 

For me, that's yoga. I can do yoga anywhere, anytime, at any intensity.

5/ Things that helped me keep the streak: 

- I told my friends/family
- I track it on my phone via @TheStreaksApp
- I block off 45 min in every day for fitness

also...

4/ And then I kept going. The more days in a row, the harder it was to break the streak. 

Over the years I added strength training, pilates, HIIT, and outdoor running.

1/ I was diagnosed with Multiple Sclerosis (MS) in November 2017.  It was (and still is) scary. Numbness, tingling, loss of vision, twitches. Feeling out of control of my own body.

Today I hit 1500 days in a row of fitness every day.
